INSERT INTO `clubs` VALUES (1,'Tottenham Hotspur','/images/logos/Tottenham_Hotspur.svg',1882,'Tottenham Hotspur Stadium',62850,'Their new stadium, opened in 2019, features a first-of-its-kind retractable pitch, revealing a second surface for NFL games and concerts. It is the third-largest football stadium in England and the largest club ground in London. Tottenham Hotspur is the 2025 UEFA Europa League winner, defeating Manchester United 1-0 in the final on Wednesday, May 21, 2025, with a goal by Brennan Johnson. This victory marked their first major trophy in 17 years and their first continental silverware since 1984.','https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/','Spurs','/images/stadiums/Tottenham_Hotspur_Stadium.png','#ffffff','#000080','Thomas Frank',1),(2,'Leeds United','/images/logos/Leeds_United.svg',1919,'Elland Road',37645,'Leeds United Football Club, founded in 1919, is one of England’s most historic clubs, known for its golden era in the 1960s and 1970s under Don Revie, when they won two league titles, an FA Cup, and reached the European Cup final. The club is based in Leeds, West Yorkshire, and plays its home matches at Elland Road, a stadium famous for its passionate atmosphere and a capacity of over 37,000. Leeds United has a fierce rivalry with Manchester United and is celebrated for its loyal fanbase, as well as producing legendary players like Billy Bremner, Jack Charlton, and more recently Kalvin Phillips.','https://www.leedsunited.com/en','The Whites','/images/stadiums/Elland_Road.png','#ffffff','#2245f7','Daniel Farke',5),(3,'Arsenal','/images/logos/Arsenal.svg',1886,'Emirates Stadium',60704,'Arsenal completed the 2003–04 Premier League season without losing a single match, earning the nickname The Invincibles. Founded by munitions workers as Dial Square, the club became the first from southern England to join the Football League in 1893. Legendary manager Herbert Chapman revolutionized tactics (the WM formation) and aesthetics (adding white sleeves and brighter red shirts) in the 1930s.','https://www.arsenal.com/','The Gunners','/images/stadiums/Emirates_Stadium.png','#fc0303','#fcfcfc','Mikel Arteta',1),(4,'Liverpool','/images/logos/Liverpool.svg',1892,'Anfield',61276,'Liverpool Football Club, founded in 1892, is one of the most successful clubs in English and European football, with 19 league titles, 8 FA Cups, and 6 UEFA Champions League trophies—most recently winning the Premier League in 2020 and the Champions League in 2019. The club is based in Liverpool, England, and plays its home matches at the iconic Anfield stadium, renowned for its passionate atmosphere and the famous \"You’ll Never Walk Alone\" anthem. Liverpool is globally recognized for its historic rivalry with Manchester United and its legacy of legendary players like Steven Gerrard, Kenny Dalglish, and Mohamed Salah.','https://www.liverpoolfc.com/','The Reds','/images/stadiums/Anfield.png','#ff0000','#ffffff','Arne Slot',3),(5,'Bournemouth','/images/logos/Bournemouth.svg',1899,'Vitality Stadium',11307,'AFC Bournemouth, founded in 1899, is a professional football club based on the south coast of England, known for its rapid rise from the lower leagues to the Premier League in recent years. The club plays its home matches at the Vitality Stadium (formerly Dean Court) and is recognized for its attractive, attacking style of play under managers like Eddie Howe. Bournemouth has established itself as a competitive Premier League side, achieving its highest-ever top-flight finish of 9th place in the 2016–17 season.','https://www.afcb.co.uk/','The Cherries','/images/stadiums/Vitality_Stadium.png','#d12e2e','#3b31c9','Andoni Iraola',12),(6,'Sunderland','/images/logos/Sunderland.svg',1879,'Stadium of Light',49000,'Sunderland AFC, founded in 1879, is one of England’s oldest and most historic football clubs, having won six top-flight league titles and two FA Cups, with its golden era in the early 20th century. The club is based in the Northeast of England and plays its home matches at the Stadium of Light, which opened in 1997 and has a capacity of nearly 50,000. Sunderland is known for its passionate fanbase and intense local rivalry with Newcastle United, known as the Tyne-Wear Derby.','https://www.safc.com/','The Black Cats','/images/stadiums/Stadium_of_Light.png','#f71d1d','#4e63ca','Régis Le Bris',7),(7,'Fulham','/images/logos/Fulham.svg',1879,'Craven Cottage',28800,'Historic Finals Without a Trophy: Fulham has reached two major finals but never clinched a major trophy—a memorable FA Cup final in 1975 (lost to West Ham) and a remarkable UEFA Europa League run in 2010, finishing as runners-up to Atlético Madrid. Riverside Home with a Unique Cottage: Craven Cottage retains its charming original structure—a literal cottage in the corner of the stadium—that dates back to when the land was a royal hunting lodge, giving the club a singular identity in English football. Steady Revival Under Marco Silva: Under Silva’s leadership, Fulham has shed its \"yo-yo\" reputation, solidifying its Premier League status, achieving club-record wins and goals in a season, and maintaining strong stability despite financial constraints.','https://www.fulhamfc.com/','The Cottagers','/images/stadiums/Craven_Cottage.png','#ffffff','#000000','Marco Silva',1),(8,'Brighton and Hove Albion','/images/logos/Brighton.svg',1901,'Falmer Stadium',31876,'Brighton qualified for European competition — the UEFA Europa League — for the first time in their history after finishing 6th in the Premier League in the 2022–23 season. The club has never won a major trophy, though they won the FA Charity Shield once (1910) and the Sussex Senior Challenge Cup multiple times. A critical moment in survival came in 1997 when Robbie Reinelt scored a decisive goal that kept Brighton in the Football League; their modern successes might have been impossible without that moment.','https://brightonandhovealbion.com/','The Seagulls','/images/stadiums/Falmer_Stadium.png','#0d67f8','#bb7fcc','Fabian Hürzeler',10),(9,'Manchester City','/images/logos/Manchester_City.svg',1880,'Etihad Stadium',52900,'Manchester City Football Club, founded in 1880, has become one of the dominant forces in English football, winning 7 Premier League titles, 7 FA Cups, and the UEFA Champions League in 2023. The club is based in Manchester and plays its home matches at the Etihad Stadium, a modern 53,000-seat venue that has been central to its recent success. Manchester City is known for its attractive, possession-based style of play under managers like Pep Guardiola, and for its intense rivalry with Manchester United in the Manchester Derby.','https://www.mancity.com/','The Citizens','/images/stadiums/Etihad_Stadium.png','#9cbff7','#000000','Pep Guardiola',2),(10,'Nottingham Forest','/images/logos/Nottingham_Forest.svg',1865,'City Ground',30404,'Nottingham Forest Football Club, founded in 1865, is one of the oldest professional football clubs in England and is best known for its golden era under Brian Clough, winning two European Cups (now Champions League) in 1979 and 1980. The club is based in Nottingham and plays its home matches at the historic City Ground, located on the banks of the River Trent. Nottingham Forest has won the English top-flight league title once (1977–78) and two FA Cups, and is renowned for its passionate fanbase and intense local rivalry with Derby County, known as the East Midlands Derby.','https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/','The Tricky Trees','/images/stadiums/City_Ground.png','#f92f2f','#ede9e9','Ange Postecoglou',8),(11,'Brentford','/images/logos/Brentford.svg',1889,'Brentford Community Stadium',17250,'Brentford’s nickname, “The Bees”, originated in the 1894–95 season when supporters misheard the school chant “Buck up Bs!” as “Buck up Bees!”—a name that stuck and now defines the club’s identity. The club moved in 2020 from its historic Griffin Park—a charming ground renowned for having a pub on each corner—to the modern Brentford Community Stadium, marking a new chapter in its infrastructure and ambitions. Brentford is notable for its innovative, data-driven approach to recruitment and player development, attracting ambitious talent and punching above its weight in recent Premier League seasons.','https://www.brentfordfc.com/en','The Bees','/images/stadiums/Brentford_Community_Stadium.png','#f53d3d','#5a3f3f','Keith Andrews',1),(12,'Everton','/images/logos/Everton.svg',1878,'Hill Dickinson Stadium',52769,'Everton Football Club, founded in 1878, is one of the oldest and most storied clubs in English football, having won nine league titles, five FA Cups, and the UEFA Cup Winners’ Cup in 1985. Based in Liverpool, Everton plays its home matches at Goodison Park, a historic stadium known for its electric atmosphere, and is set to move to a new state-of-the-art stadium at Bramley-Moore Dock. The club is famous for its fierce Merseyside Derby rivalry with Liverpool FC and has a rich history of legendary players, including Dixie Dean, Alan Ball, and Wayne Rooney.','https://www.evertonfc.com/','The Toffees','/images/stadiums/Hill_Dickinson_Stadium.png','#0535f5','#f0eacc','David Moyes',3),(13,'Crystal Palace','/images/logos/Crystal_Palace.svg',1905,'Selhurst Park',25486,'In May 2025, Crystal Palace secured the first major trophy in their 164-year history by defeating Manchester City 1-0 in the FA Cup final, with Eberechi Eze scoring the historic winning goal and Dean Henderson saving a crucial penalty. Under coach Oliver Glasner, the team ended the 2024–25 season strongly—recording six wins from their last seven matches, achieving their highest-ever Premier League points tally of 53, including a memorable 5–0 home win over Aston Villa, one of the biggest victories in club history. The club is planning a significant redevelopment of Selhurst Park, including a new main stand that would increase capacity to around 34,000, add improved hospitality facilities, a museum, and better accessibility—reflecting a major investment in the club’s future','https://www.cpfc.co.uk/','The Eagles','/images/stadiums/Selhurst_Park.png','#3542fd','#b68f25','Oliver Glasner',1),(14,'Burnley','/images/logos/Burnley.svg',1882,'Turf Moor',21944,'Burnley Football Club, founded in 1882, is one of the oldest professional clubs in England and has won the top-flight league title twice (1920–21 and 1959–60) as well as the FA Cup once (1914). The club is based in Burnley, Lancashire, and plays its home matches at Turf Moor, a historic stadium known for its traditional atmosphere and a capacity of over 21,000. Burnley is recognized for its resilient, hard-working style of play and has established itself as a regular Premier League and Championship competitor in recent years.','https://burnleyfootballclub.com/','The Clarets','/images/stadiums/Turf_Moor.png','#980639','#73b0f2','Scott Parker',11),(15,'West Ham United','/images/logos/West_Ham_United.svg',1901,'London Stadium',68013,'Origins & \"White Horse Final\": West Ham began life connected to the Thames Ironworks but formed officially as West Ham United in 1901. They played at the Memorial Grounds before moving to the Boleyn Ground in 1904. Their first FA Cup final appearance came in 1923 at the old Wembley, dubbed the “White Horse Final” due to a mounted police horse clearing spectators off the pitch—a memorable chapter in both club and football history. Stadium Transition & Atmosphere: In 2016, the club moved from the historic Boleyn Ground (Upton Park) to the London Stadium—a converted Olympic venue. While it boosted capacity and facilities, debates about the stadium’s atmosphere and fit have persisted among fans and pundits. Sustainability Upgrades: The club’s London Stadium recently received a major sustainability upgrade: a £4.35 million installation of solar panels covering 6,500 m² of its roof. It’s the largest solar deployment at any UK stadium and expected to generate 850,000 kWh per year, significantly reducing carbon emissions and energy costs.','https://www.whufc.com/','The Hammers','/images/stadiums/London_Stadium.png','#a03131','#e5dac8','Graham Potter',1),(16,'Chelsea','/images/logos/Chelsea.svg',1905,'Stamford Bridge',40341,'Chelsea Football Club, founded in 1905, is one of England’s most successful football clubs, having won six Premier League titles, eight FA Cups, and two UEFA Champions League trophies (in 2012 and 2021). The club is based in Fulham, West London, and plays its home matches at Stamford Bridge, a stadium with a capacity of over 40,000. Chelsea is known for its global fanbase and has been home to legendary players such as Frank Lampard, John Terry, and Didier Drogba.','https://www.chelseafc.com/en','The Pensioners','/images/stadiums/Stamford_Bridge.png','#1d49fc','#fafafa','Enzo Maresca',1),(17,'Newcastle United','/images/logos/Newcastle_United.svg',1892,'St James\' Park',52305,'Historic Trophy Breakthrough: Under Eddie Howe’s leadership, Newcastle ended a 56-year trophy drought by winning the EFL (Carabao) Cup in March 2025 — Howe became the first English manager to win such a major domestic trophy since 2008. Resurgence to Europe: Howe guided Newcastle to a Champions League qualification for the first time in years, marking a strong resurgence in club status on the European stage. Fortress at Home & Tactical Identity: St James\' Park is renowned for its atmosphere, and Howe’s strategic adaptability—combining pragmatic tactics with long-throws and flexible setups—has helped Maxwell survive squad challenges and maintain strong home performances.','https://www.newcastleunited.com/en','The Magpies','/images/stadiums/St_James_Park.png','#000000','#45c47c','Eddie Howe',6),(18,'Aston Villa','/images/logos/Aston_Villa.svg',1874,'Villa Park',42900,'Aston Villa is a pioneering English football club that was a founding member of both the Football League and the Premier League, and is one of only six English teams to win the European Cup. They lifted the trophy on May 26, 1982, with Peter Withe\'s goal in Rotterdam, beating Bayern Munich 1-0 to win the competition. \r\nAston Villa holds the record for the most league goals scored by any team in the English top flight, with 128 goals in the 1930-31 season.\r\n','https://www.avfc.co.uk/','The Villans','/images/stadiums/Villa_Park.png','#722745','#f1ebf9','Unai Emery',4),(19,'Wolverhampton Wanderers','/images/logos/Wolverhampton_Wanderers.svg',1877,'Molineux Stadium',31750,'Historic Home Ground: Molineux is one of England\'s earliest purpose-built football stadiums (opened in 1889). It was among the first British clubs to install floodlights in the 1950s and even hosted early televised midweek friendlies. Managerial Turnaround: Pereira inherited a team in deep relegation trouble (just 9 points from 16 matches). He secured their Premier League survival with key wins—including a 1–0 triumph at Manchester United—lifting them 12 points clear of relegation by April 2025. Strategic Rebuild Ahead of 2025–26: Looking ahead to the 2025-26 season, Wolves are cautious but hopeful, banking on the leadership of Pereira, smart recruitment (including signing Emmanuel Agbadou and Marshall Munetsi), and contributions from leading players like João Gomes to stabilize the club in the top flight.','https://www.wolves.co.uk/','Wolves','/images/stadiums/Molineux_Stadium.png','#e6bd28','#050505','Vítor Pereira',9),(20,'Manchester United','/images/logos/Manchester_United.svg',1878,'Old Trafford',74310,'Manchester United Football Club, founded in 1878 as Newton Heath, is one of the most successful and widely supported football clubs in the world, with a record 20 English league titles, 12 FA Cups, and 3 UEFA Champions League trophies. The club is based in Manchester, England, and plays its home matches at Old Trafford, the largest club football stadium in the UK with a capacity of over 74,000. Manchester United is globally renowned for its rich history, legendary managers like Sir Alex Ferguson, and iconic players such as George Best, Eric Cantona, and Cristiano Ronaldo, as well as its fierce rivalry with Liverpool and Manchester City.','https://www.manutd.com/','The Red Devils','/images/stadiums/Old_Trafford.png','#f90101','#ffffff','Ruben Amorim',2);
